				\begin{document}$$ f=\frac{N_m}{N_i} $$\end{document}f=NmNi

FIC was determined using the following formula to evaluate the information of medicinal plants distributed between informants and to determine the homogeneity of informant’s knowledge on medicinal plants.
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{FIC}=\frac{N_{ur}-{N}_t}{N_{ur}-1} $$\end{document}FIC=Nur−NtNur−1

Each species mentioned by an informant within one use category was a use report (UR). Cultural importance index (CI) was used to indicate the spread of the use (number of informants) of each species as well as to determine diversity of uses.
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
